article.headline: Pacific 68, Cal State Northridge 64
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. (AP) -- Anthony Brown scored a game-high 21 points to lead Pacific to a 68-64 victory over Cal State Northridge in a Big West Conference opener Saturday night. Joe Ford came off the bench to score a career-high 10 points for the Tigers, the three-time defending Big West regular-season champions who stretched their conference winning streak to 11 games dating back to last season. Pacific (4-9), which snapped a six-game losing streak, has won 48 of its past 51 regular-season Big West games. Terrell Jones had 17 points and Jonathan Heard scored 16 for Cal State Northridge (6-6). Heards jump-shot tied the game for the 12th and final time at 58-58 with 5:17 to play, but Brown and C.J. Morgan (9 points) combined to score the next seven points to put Pacific in command. Brown, a sophomore forward, also had a game-high nine rebounds. Northridge got within 65-63 with a minute remaining, but the Matadors could get no closer. The game was tied six times and featured seven lead changes before Northridge ended the first half with an 8-1 run to take a 36-30 advantage at the break. Jones came off the bench to score 12 points in the first half, making three free throws and a layup in the final two minutes to put the Matadors in control. But Pacific immediately erased that lead with a 12-2 run to begin the second half, and the Tigers never trailed by more than two points the rest of the way.
